Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.62,0:00:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Dr. David Hawkins. I've been a psychiatrist for the last 35 years.\NI've worked in the fields of psychoanalysis, psychopharmacology, psychotherapy, group therapy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.58,0:00:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I did a lot of research in the nature of relationship between nutrition and brain chemistry.\NAnd for the last 10 years, I've been working in the research into the nature of consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.40,0:00:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and its relationship to that field of knowledge referred to by the world as spiritual.\NAnd today's talk will be on giving up being old, letting go of the aging process,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.06,0:00:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,how to identify with that aspect of yourself which is real,\Nand let go of those identifications with that which is unreal.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.88,0:00:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we'll be talking about the relationship between body, mind, and spirit.\NWhat is the true relationship, and how does that relate to our topic for today?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.79,0:01:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be looking at where is it that man experiences experience,\Nbecause if we address the results of our research to that area where man really experiences his experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.43,0:01:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we find that we are not subject to many things that the world holds to be inevitable.\NWe see that aging is a series of identifications.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.49,0:01:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's buying into a whole series of programs, stereotypes, behavior patterns.\NIt's buying life scripts.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.33,0:01:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That which really experiences life has no age.\NAnd it is not subject to aging.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.57,0:01:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have to ask ourselves, are we that which we are experiencing, or are we the experiencer?\NWe'll look into the middle-aged myth, the health patterns, sexual patterns,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.31,0:01:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,so weight problems that supposedly occur in middle age.\NWe'll look into the statement that the body does what the mind believes,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.59,0:02:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll look into the physics of that.\NWe'll look into the fact that the body is really the effect and not the cause,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.10,0:02:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's not the cause.\NWe'll look into the fact that the body is really the effect and not the cause,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.58,0:02:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,subject to what we hold in mind.\NWe'll look at the fact that we have freedom of choice to elect these various patterns.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.02,0:02:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll look at the adopting of family patterns\Nand the influence that they have had on our thoughts and beliefs about longevity
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.12,0:02:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and what that looks like.\NThe importance of feeling that your life is a contribution, a sharing,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.13,0:02:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that it makes a difference, that it is of value.\NWe'll look at some experiments from hypnosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.93,0:02:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll look at some odd things that have occurred in science\Nthat have occurred in our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.49,0:02:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll look at a clinical example called progeria and what that means to us.\NWe'll look at aging as a class phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.55,0:02:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll look at sex and age.\NAnd so today we'll cover this whole field which preoccupies everyone as he grows older,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.43,0:02:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the facts, the fantasies.\NHow can this be handled coming from our knowledge of the nature of consciousness itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.33,0:03:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we'll be referring, as we have in these other talks,\Nto a map of consciousness, something we have found,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.49,0:03:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and extremely useful.\NIt gives us an orientation to the whole subject of human behavior and who am I.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.00,0:03:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we have really a mathematical model\Nin which we have worked out the relative energy fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.34,0:03:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the directions of the energy fields of these levels of consciousness,\Nand we've worked out numerically their relative power,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.02,0:03:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,starting with death at zero and enlightenment at 600, for instance.\NWe find that,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.10,0:03:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,apathy at 50 has half the power of fear,\Nand fear calibrates at 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.52,0:03:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We find that fear has half the energy of courage.\NSo we find that neutral, where everything is just okay with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.16,0:03:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,has half the energy of love.\NWe notice that below this level of courage,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.16,0:04:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the capacity to tell the truth,\Nthat all the energy fields are reversed and in a negative direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.56,0:04:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And we notice critically,\Nabove this level that all the energy fields go to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.76,0:04:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, those plus positive energy fields\Nare those which nurture, support, and value life and hold it as sacred.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.86,0:04:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,These energy fields below are those which are opposed to life,\Ndo not support life,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.26,0:04:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and in fact, at the very bottom, become destruction.\NLoss of energy, loss of spirit, deflation, entrapment, inflation and expansion
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.86,0:04:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,are all negative processes.\NAnd they lead to viewing the world in a negative way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.36,0:04:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They lead to seeing God in a very negative way.\NAnd so, in our talk today, we'll be going back to this chart,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.46,0:04:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to this map of consciousness,\Nand so that we have a way of orienting our knowledge of this whole field.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.22,0:05:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's necessary to restate then the relationship between body, mind and spirit,\Nto see what this really means, because it is very important
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.45,0:05:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in looking at our subject for today.\NIt's necessary to know and to realize through your own inner reflection and contemplation
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.47,0:05:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that the body is unable to experience itself.\NWe've said this in all of our talks, but it cannot bear repeating too often.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.97,0:05:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The body has no capacity to experience itself.\NOur knowledge about the body, of what's going on with the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.62,0:05:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming from its sensations.\NThe sensations themselves, in and of themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.02,0:05:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,have no capacity to experience themselves.\NThat experience has to go on in something that is greater than the body and its sensations,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.52,0:05:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,its sensory mechanisms, and that is mind itself.\NIt's because of mind that you're aware of what is going on within the sensations,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.56,0:06:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and the sensations are telling you what is happening within the body.\NMind itself, as curious as it may seem, has no capacity to experience itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.25,0:06:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,A thought cannot experience its own thoughtness.\NA feeling cannot experience its own feelingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.75,0:06:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,A memory cannot experience its own memoryness.\NMind itself, in order to be experienced,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.75,0:06:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,has to be experienced by something that is greater than itself,\Nand that is the energy field of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.75,0:06:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness itself being greater than mind and more inclusive.\NConsciousness itself, how do we know what we are conscious of?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.13,0:06:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Is coming from an infinite field with no limitations whatsoever called awareness.\NIt's because of awareness that we know what is going on in consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.13,0:06:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It is because of consciousness that we know what is going on in mind.\NIt is because of mind that we're aware of what's going on with sensations.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.13,0:07:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of sensations we're aware of what's going on with the body.\NConsequently, that which we are, that which is aware,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.13,0:07:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that which we really mean by the ultimate I, the infinite self,\Nthat which is aware and conscious,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.63,0:07:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is far removed, many levels removed, as you can see, from the body.\NThe interesting thing is that the body, one law of consciousness is,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.28,0:07:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the body does what the mind holds.\NWe're only subject to what the mind is holding.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.78,0:07:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, the body, being like a puppet, is controlled by mind.\NIt is controlled both consciously and unconsciously.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.78,0:07:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Few people realize the power of mind over body.\NWhen we look back at our field of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.28,0:07:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,when we look at this map,\Nwe'll see that the physical body has a relative energy of about 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.28,0:08:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mind itself is up here in the 400s,\Nalthough we don't have it on the blackboard because we only have limited space.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.28,0:08:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All the levels of mind are energy fields in the 400s.\NThe energy field of the body is neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.78,0:08:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It is neither positive or negative.\NA thought then held in mind, if we just look at the physics of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.28,0:08:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,held from an energy of 400 then dominates the body,\Nwhich only has an energy field of 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.78,0:08:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, the beliefs, the ideas, the thoughts, the configurations,\Nthe patterns, the scripts that we hold in mind are adopted by the body
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.28,0:08:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and begin to reflect in the body's physical appearance.\NAnd we certainly have covered this in our talks on health,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.28,0:08:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in our talks on illness,\Nand in our talks on giving up the various diseases,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.78,0:08:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in which I shared a lot of my personal experience as well as research.\NSo this principle will be very important for us to look at today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.78,0:08:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll demonstrate it with clinical examples,\Nand we'll give you ways to verify it for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.28,0:09:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,How to undo the middle age myth,\Nthe whole idea of decrepit old age,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.78,0:09:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the idea of failing health,\Nthe belief system that all these things are inevitable,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.78,0:09:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that they must be part and parcel of the body process itself,\Nlittle realizing that they are actually coming from mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.78,0:09:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we come across the principle of where is the source,\Nthat mind is the creator and that the physical body is the effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.78,0:09:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Mind is where causation occurs and the physical body is in effect.\NThe fact that the material world then is at the effect
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.28,0:09:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is the result of what is held in mind.\NAnd we can demonstrate this with very simple clinical examples such as hypnosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.78,0:09:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We see in hypnosis, for instance, we can take an old person who is quite feeble.\NHe walks in the office and he says,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.78,0:09:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like me to sit here?\NCould I sit in this chair here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.78,0:10:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And he sits down as though he barely has the strength and the power to sit in the chair.\NAnd we put him under hypnosis and we tell him he's 35 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.28,0:10:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we induce amnesia.\NSo he doesn't remember what the suggestion was.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.78,0:10:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we wake him up from his hypnotic state.\NAnd we say, Would you like a glass of water?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.78,0:10:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And he says, Oh yes, I'd like a glass of water.\NAnd he walks over to the bubbler and he takes a glass and he fills it and he sits down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.78,0:10:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And the feeble old man is gone.\NWhere is all the shaking? Where is all the trembling?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.28,0:10:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is all the weakness? Where is all that decrepitness?\NWhat has happened to the feeble old man? He seems to have disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.28,0:10:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We can see with the clinical example then, through the hypnotic state,\Nthat the mind is reflecting exactly what the mind believes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.69,0:10:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The body is reflecting exactly what the mind believes.\NThe way it stands. The way it holds itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.69,0:10:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The attitude towards the body.\NThe old person is looking at the body as though it's frail.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.19,0:11:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, they're preoccupied. They might fall and break their hip.\NAnd thereby holding that in mind and bringing it into their life experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.19,0:11:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So with hypnosis we see a very good example then.\NAnd we've used also the example in other talks of the multiple personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.69,0:11:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Where one of the personalities has totally different views about health and life and aging\Nthan the second personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.69,0:11:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the one personality is in the body, the body reflects what that personality believes.\NSo if one personality believes in asthma, while that personality is in the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.69,0:11:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the person literally has asthma.\NBut when that personality is replaced by a more pleasant personality
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.69,0:11:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that doesn't have a belief in these psychosomatic illnesses,\Nthen we see the asthma is not present.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.69,0:11:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And that person has no allergies.\NConsequently, the physical body is reflecting exactly what our belief systems are.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.69,0:11:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll look at how did these belief systems arise.\NFirst of all, that we have an option.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.82,0:12:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the mind concludes, I don't have any options.\NThe naive mind thinks I'm at the effect of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.27,0:12:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm at the effect of the ongoingness of time.\NIn this case, the mind is giving away its power to the calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.27,0:12:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It says, it pictures as the years go by, the body must of necessity get older.\NWell, we see a very interesting clinical example in a scientific condition called progeria.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.04,0:12:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In which the person progressively ages and becomes an extremely old, old person by the age of 5, 6, 7, 8, 9\Nand often dead by age 10 of old age.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.66,0:12:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Literal old age, decrepit old age by age 10.\NAnd so we see an interesting example.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.16,0:13:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,How can old age and actually death from old age occur in a span of only 10 calendar years?\NIf calendar years were cause and physical body was at the effect of the calendar, no such thing could occur.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.66,0:13:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The only reason to bring these up is to\Nbegin to open the mind to see that we have options.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.16,0:13:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,To see that that which we believe, that which we buy into,\Nthat which we allow ourselves to be programmed by,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.66,0:13:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,now becomes the source. It becomes the program.\NIt becomes the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.16,0:13:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And this script begins to express itself on the physical level.\NWhen we see it occurring on the physical level,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.16,0:13:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind, because of its naivete, concludes that causation,\Nis happening on the physical level.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.16,0:13:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So the naive mind sees causality as A causes B causes C\Nwithin the physical realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.26,0:13:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The turning of the calendar, the turning of the seasons,\Nis causing, on the physical level then, the aging process of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.92,0:14:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It sees causality on the physical level as A causes B causes C.\NAnd closer to reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.53,0:14:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth is that something from a higher level is causing,\Nsequentially, both A, B and C.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.26,0:14:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Cause is on this level, effect is on this level.\NIf I hold a concept in mind that goes A, B, C,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.26,0:14:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,then within the physical world what we see is first A, then B, then C.\NThe left brain, because it thinks linearly
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.10,0:14:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and projects its concepts onto the phenomena of the world,\Nholds, therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.10,0:14:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that A must cause B cause C,\Nnever suspecting that causality of A, B, C
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.10,0:14:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming from a different level altogether.\NSo the level of cause, where the power is,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.10,0:14:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is the level of mind.\NThe world of the physical is the world of effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.58,0:14:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It creates A, B, C.\NSo if I hold a pattern in mind of what aging looks like,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.58,0:15:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,what I think it must be and what must happen,\NI create on the physical level A, B, C.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.58,0:15:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The decrepit, feeble old man,\Nbecause in his childhood that's what old people looked like.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.74,0:15:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He was convinced.\NThat's what you look like when you're 80.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.74,0:15:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And so when he was 80, that's exactly what he looked like.\NSo if we could look back into his mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.24,0:15:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,go into his mind and see his pictures\Nof what does an old man look like,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.74,0:15:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,we would see exactly what an old man looks like\Nbecause he's standing there right in front of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.24,0:15:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That was his picture of what it looks like to get old.\NThe body demonstrating what the mind believes
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.24,0:15:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,is an experiment done with the menstrual periods in women\Nin which they were given an injection.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.49,0:15:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,They were told that this injection would result\Nin their skipping their next menstrual period.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.49,0:15:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And so what happened was they were given an injection of a placebo.\NAnd of those people given the injection of a placebo,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.59,0:16:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,all of them experienced either skipping the menstrual period\Nor a delay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.09,0:16:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I think 85% skipped the next menstrual period\Nand 15% experienced a great delay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.09,0:16:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So these examples are not exceptions.\NThese are...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.09,0:16:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What we're interested in is the basic principle.\NThe basic principle is that this is going on all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.09,0:16:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind is continuously reflecting\Nthe patterns and the beliefs of what is being held in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.09,0:16:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,These clinical examples from hypnosis\Nand research experiments are merely isolated examples
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.32,0:16:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,where you can see it clearly.\NBut you can see then if under hypnosis
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.36,0:16:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the body will do exactly what the mind believes.\NFor instance, you can put a patient under
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.36,0:16:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell him he's allergic to roses.\NAnd when he wakes up, his nose will stuff up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.36,0:16:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll go into hay fever and have an asthma attack\Nright there within the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.36,0:17:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been done many times and it's historically recorded\Nin the annals of psychoanalysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.43,0:17:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This is always going on.\NAnd so now you begin to get a feel
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.43,0:17:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,for what we're talking about.\NThat the constant programming is coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.43,0:17:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The expectations of middle age and old age\Nand what this is supposed to mean
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.43,0:17:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,are now bought by the mind out of its naivete.\NAnd as we've said in other talks,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.96,0:17:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the basic principles of consciousness itself\Nis its intrinsic innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.32,0:17:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because the mind is innocent\Nthat we have to carefully begin to watch it and guard it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.32,0:17:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to become like its mother.\NOur mind is like an innocent kid
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.82,0:17:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,who goes out in the world\Nand believes everything it hears.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.32,0:17:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It believes every billboard.\NIt believes every commercial.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.32,0:17:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It believes every remark that people make.\NIt believes what it sees.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.32,0:17:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no way to evaluate it.\NIt has no sense of discrimination.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.38,0:17:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we have to begin to sort of take responsibility\Nand say, I can see that my mind
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.88,0:18:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and its intrinsic innocence\Nbecause the innocence of the mind of the child
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.88,0:18:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is still with us throughout life.\NAnd I'd better start looking into what it's been buying.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.07,0:18:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we look at the lives of many people\Nthat are very creative.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.07,0:18:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see that, characteristically,\Nthey live well into their 90s.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.07,0:18:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And frequently they get married at 85\Nand start having children at 90.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.57,0:18:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And Dr. John Diamond, a physician,\Nhas written a couple of books about that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.57,0:18:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in his books about behavioral kinesiology\Nand the energy of life
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.57,0:18:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in which he does a whole chapter on that.\NHe made a study of the life patterns
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.57,0:18:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of those who are into classical music,\Nconductors and composers and performers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.57,0:18:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And he found that, characteristically,\Nthey all live to a very old age
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.07,0:18:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and remain productive.\NWe think nothing of an 86-year-old conductor
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.57,0:18:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,leading a whole symphony orchestra,\Nhaving a 34-year-old wife
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.57,0:18:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and a young baby at home.\NWe all just sort of know
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.76,0:19:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that that goes with that lifestyle.\NWriters who live to a very advanced age.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.76,0:19:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,People into research and physics\Nwho live to a very ripe old age.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.76,0:19:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Performers.\NWe think of George Burns, Fred Astaire.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.76,0:19:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Age means nothing at all, then, as such.\NIn other words, the numerical, chronological age
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.26,0:19:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,has no power within it.\NBut our beliefs about that,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.26,0:19:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,how we hold that,\Nhow we genuflect to all the belief systems
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.30,0:19:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that go with that,\Nthat we've bought throughout the years,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.30,0:19:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that does have power.\NHow is it that some people are dancing
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.30,0:19:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and performing at 90,\Nand other people at 59
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.30,0:19:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,are ready for the grave?\NI have a friend who, at age 59,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.36,0:19:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,looks like he's about 75.\NIt's like life is all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.36,0:19:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He's already had a couple of coronary bypass operations.\NThe way he holds himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.50,0:20:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the weakness and the whole body stance,\Ntells you what he believes old age must entail.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.04,0:20:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So the first thing we have to see\Nis that we have options.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.04,0:20:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We have options.\NWe can choose to be different.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.54,0:20:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We can choose to let go of the belief systems in our family.\NWe can begin to see now and look back
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.61,0:20:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,where did these belief systems about\Nwhat middle age and the aging process,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.61,0:20:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,where did they come from?\NWhat constitutes them?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.61,0:20:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We look at our own childhood now\Nand look at our grandparents.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.11,0:20:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And what was our relationship with our grandparents?\NAnd at that time, our parents were middle aged.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.11,0:20:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we look at our middle aged parents,\Nremember the pattern,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.11,0:20:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,we see that like a photograph,\Nthe negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.61,0:20:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It means what? A beer belly?\NIt means sitting home,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.11,0:20:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling tired and discouraged\Nand watching the television set
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.61,0:20:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and complaining about life.\NDoes it mean overhearing remarks?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.61,0:20:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't have the energy for that anymore.\NGetting the thought that well,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.61,0:21:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you're over the hill\Nand the men start to wink at each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.11,0:21:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey George, what are you,\Na little over the hill there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.11,0:21:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning middle age,\Nforget about sex life.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.11,0:21:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All these programs are going into the impressionable mind\Nof the naive child.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.11,0:21:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He's creating a picture\Nwhat mother looks like,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.61,0:21:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,tired and bedraggled.\NShe no longer cares for her appearance,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.11,0:21:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't bother going to the beautician anymore\Nbecause middle age to her now means
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.61,0:21:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of retiring from life, you see.\NAnd we see the people looking forward to retirement
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.12,0:21:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and what their views of that are.\NThe confusion of retiring from the job
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.12,0:21:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,with retiring from life.\NHow many people do you know at age 65
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.12,0:21:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,retired not just from jobs,\Nbut they retired from life itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.62,0:21:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole attitude is,\Nwe'll go to sunset hills now
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.62,0:21:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and slowly wait for the sun to set.\NWe'll join the old people's
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.62,0:21:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,fade out club\Nand we get progressively weaker
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.12,0:22:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and watch each other go.\NThat's an option.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.07,0:22:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,George Burns didn't buy that option.\NFred Astaire didn't buy that option.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.89,0:22:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The great composers and writers,\Nthink of all the politicians
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.39,0:22:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and the powers that run this world\Nwell into their 60s, 70s and 80s.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.39,0:22:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,As they got older,\Ntheir power, their wisdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.89,0:22:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,their ability in the world\Ngrew ever stronger, not weaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.14,0:22:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at all the thought systems and beliefs\Nabout what is supposed to happen to the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.21,0:22:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All the thoughts of what we think\Naging must entail.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.30,0:22:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was young,\NI heard about the prostate trouble
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.30,0:22:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of all the grandfathers and men in my family.\NAll the men from age 45 or 50 on
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.30,0:22:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,had prostate trouble.\NAnd they complained about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.35,0:22:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And women's complaints about their\NGU system and GI system,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.35,0:22:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,all these things that supposedly go with old age.\NAnd when I got to be 50,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.85,0:23:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't realize it,\Nbut I was holding all those thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.35,0:23:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in my mind too.\NAnd at age 50,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.35,0:23:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly I became a very middle-aged,\Naging person.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.85,0:23:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,At age 50,\Nsuddenly my hands and my feet
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.35,0:23:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,were cold all the time.\NI was exhausted all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.35,0:23:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I was tired.\NLibido went out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.85,0:23:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The prostate became enlarged.\NAll kinds of physical diseases began to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.35,0:23:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,All the things that fit my picture\Nof middle age,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.35,0:23:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,discouragement and depression.\NAt middle age, the picture was
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.35,0:23:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you're very tired out by the world.\NYou're exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.85,0:23:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You lay on the couch and you can barely get up.\NYou complain about your prostate.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.35,0:23:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And you infer by various jokes and innuendos\Nthat sex is, you know, a thing of the past now
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.80,0:23:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because older people don't have that.\NYou see?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.80,0:23:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Like nuns don't go to the bathroom.\NAll those childhood beliefs, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.79,0:23:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it that all this came to pass then?\NIt came to pass because that was my picture
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.29,0:24:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of what it meant to be middle-aged.\NAnd so, to begin with then,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.29,0:24:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to look at what are our pictures?\NWhat was our relationship with our parents?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.79,0:24:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we love them?\NInteresting enough that love can be
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.79,0:24:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the very reason for that identification.\NIt's because we love them
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.29,0:24:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that we pattern ourself after them.\NIf you admire your father
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.79,0:24:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and then he develops this middle-age pattern,\Nof your admiration and love for him
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.79,0:24:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and family loyalty,\Nyou identify with it and you pick up this pattern,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.79,0:24:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,not for negative reasons,\Nbut out of innocence and out of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.79,0:24:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The same with your relationship with your grandparents.\NYou get an idea of what old age looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.82,0:24:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I had a relatively negative view of middle age.\NBut I had a relatively positive view
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.32,0:24:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of old age.\NAnd therefore, I've always looked forward to old age.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.32,0:24:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,At 76, my grandfather was up on the roof\Nputting on a new roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.32,0:24:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,My other grandfather was dignified and elegant.\NAnd so, I looked forward to old age.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.32,0:25:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the time when you can put on your spots\Nand your spats and your best hat
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.32,0:25:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and dress up and wear your best clothes\Nand live a really aristocratic, enjoyable life.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.32,0:25:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,For once, you can really just be who you really are.\NIt's going to be over before long
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.82,0:25:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore, you don't have to cater to anybody anymore.\NYou can really be elegant
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.32,0:25:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and a very loving and wonderful person.\NSo, old age, to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.82,0:25:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,was not something of a faltering decrepitude.\NIt has been for other people, however.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.51,0:25:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, we see that we have an option.\NIt's who you loved and who you identified with.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.51,0:25:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all the programming that we've gotten from television,\Nyou know, the movies, the image of what aging means
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.01,0:25:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and all this kind of thing.\NThe television commercials,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.51,0:25:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,all those things that are designed\Nto appeal to those fears of aging.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.51,0:25:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, what we fear, we hold in mind\Nand what we hold in mind tends to manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.51,0:25:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, our fears of old age,\Nthe very things we begin to fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.51,0:26:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,are the very things that begin to manifest.\NWe have to go back to the realization
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.12,0:26:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have an option.\NWe don't have to buy any of these pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.12,0:26:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever picture we buy\Nis what is going to manifest in our life.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.12,0:26:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, we have to be careful.\NAbout what we buy into.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.12,0:26:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, therefore, we sort of become\Nthe guardian of our mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.62,0:26:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We look at it and see,\Nwhat does it believe?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.62,0:26:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We forgive it for what it picked up over the years.\NIt didn't know of its own innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.12,0:26:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, it picked up all these programs\Nand stories and scripts.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.12,0:26:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And unwittingly, we found that we were beginning\Nto act them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.18,0:26:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if we want to know what life scripts we bought,\Nall we have to do is look at our life
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.84,0:26:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and look at our physical self\Nand the physical self then,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.84,0:26:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,being a reflection of what we have bought,\Ntells us what we've bought.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.97,0:26:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,See, we may not be able to remember it.\NMany of these things, we have amnesia.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.47,0:26:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Remarks overheard throughout childhood.\NPeople look into their memory and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.62,0:27:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember ever believing such a thing.\NWe're unconscious and don't remember most of our life.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.12,0:27:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize that you have amnesia really for most of your life.\NBecause of the millions and millions of things
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.62,0:27:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can remember,\Nwhat you don't realize is,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.62,0:27:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in one day, look at how many seconds there are.\NDo you remember what happened each second in each day?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.62,0:27:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You're lucky if you can remember\Nwhat you had for breakfast yesterday, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.01,0:27:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, a great deal of what went on in your life\Nis forgotten, not totally, not actually forgotten,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.01,0:27:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but you might say operationally forgotten\Nand that it's not available for immediate recall.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.39,0:27:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If we look at the body then,\Nwe'll see what the programs were that it picked up,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.89,0:27:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,what its belief systems were,\Nwhat it thought was valuable,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.89,0:27:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe that which it actually loved,\Nor its reverse, that which it feared
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.89,0:27:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and brought about into manifestation\Nbecause the fear was holding it in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.18,0:28:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that the patterns of aging\Nalso follow a certain class phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.68,0:28:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see a changing picture of age and aging.\NWe see increasing longevity,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.18,0:28:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,it is now very common for people to live longer\Nand even though they live longer,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.68,0:28:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to be energetic and very much alive\Ninto very advanced age.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.68,0:28:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We see this is characteristic of the upper classes.\NWe see it as characteristic of those who are aristocratic.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.71,0:28:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,When I said I had grandfathers\Nwho were very lively and spry in their old age
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.21,0:28:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and were very elegant in their style and their dress,\Nthat's a certain lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.71,0:28:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,which we classify as aristocratic.\NIt means holding the value of one's life now
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.82,0:28:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and seeing old age as one of increasing stature and value.\NWe contrast this with a different class view
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.45,0:29:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,where the class where your power and value in the world\Ncomes out of your physical strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.45,0:29:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And there we see the more rapid aging patterns.\NWe see, for instance,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.95,0:29:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in sports figures where at age 32 they're already old\Nand at 40, forget it,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.95,0:29:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,they're an old man in that sports field.\NWe see certain classes of laboring people
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.95,0:29:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,where at age 65 when you retire it's pretty much over.\NAnd from 65 on this pattern then
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.95,0:29:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,of moving into Sunset Hills and the beer belly\Nand you see indolence
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.95,0:29:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and the loss of energy, the loss of interest,\Nthe loss of aliveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.95,0:29:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The giving up of life,\Nas though retiring from the job means retiring from life.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.95,0:29:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,As though the job was the only thing that gave meaning and value to life.\NAnd now that one is not classified anymore as a worker in quotes,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.45,0:30:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,one no longer has value in the world.\NThe failure there to look at oneself in a more holistic total way,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.95,0:30:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to see value as something other than productivity in the workforce,\Nto see the value of one's life as something other than
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.95,0:30:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the capacity to bring home a paycheck every Friday,\Nto see oneself as something other than just provider
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.90,0:30:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,or just mother of the children.\NAnd so we see the pattern in women
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.90,0:30:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the aging process doesn't really start\Nuntil the children grow up and leave home.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.90,0:30:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And then suddenly she joins her husband\Nin this retiring from life.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.90,0:30:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He retires from the job.\NShe's now retired from the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.40,0:30:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,His mother.\NBoth of them are now unemployed with no value in their own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.40,0:30:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And although they make a few sporadic jabs\Nat being of some use in society,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.40,0:30:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't really believe it.\NAnd therefore the aging then becomes progressive and rapid.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.40,0:31:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And many of them die, of course,\Nwithin one year of retirement.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.90,0:31:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The coronary heart attack within one year of retirement\Nis much higher than any other bracket
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.90,0:31:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,amongst a certain class of workers.\NAnd so we have to look earlier in life
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.40,0:31:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and we have to constantly challenge these belief systems\Nto discover something about our life that is of such value
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.40,0:31:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that whether we work, whether we bring home a paycheck,\Nwhether we're raising children,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.40,0:31:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,whether we're following a traditional,\Nsolid, middle-class American way of life or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.40,0:31:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that our life still has value.\NThat we see that we're making a difference in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.40,0:31:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That our life is significant.\NThe willingness to share our life with others
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.90,0:31:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a source of enthusiasm,\Nto contribute to the life of those around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.40,0:31:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to reevaluate now the value of our life\Nand recontextualize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.40,0:31:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Come from a different way of being with it.\NHow to look at it differently
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.90,0:32:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,so as to give it a different value in our own eyes.\NHow to raise our own energy pattern
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.40,0:32:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,by coming from a different way of looking at it.\NWe said that one is not really subject
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.26,0:32:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to anything but what is held in mind.\NThat we can identify these belief systems and patterns,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.79,0:32:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have the option to change them.\NThe choice is up to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.29,0:32:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We can be very active and vigorous into old age,\Nhave a very significant and valuable life,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.79,0:32:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,highly enjoyable.\NOur physical health can continue right to the very end.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.71,0:32:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,When we say this, some people automatically get a resentment.\NAnd what is the resentment coming from?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.21,0:32:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's coming from the fact that they were looking forward\Nto these disabilities of old age.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.71,0:32:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They were looking forward to the secondary gains and benefits\Nthat they would get out of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.21,0:33:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They picture themselves as somewhat feeble and old\Nand now people start looking out for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.21,0:33:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're going to get a lot of attention.\NPeople will hold open doors,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.21,0:33:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,put the packages in the car for you,\Ngive you 10% off on your groceries.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.71,0:33:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,There'll be all kinds of credits and things\Nand aids that come to you now
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.71,0:33:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because of your disability.\NAnd so when you see the secondary gain,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.71,0:33:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to look at that and say,\Nwhat was I hoping to get out of, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.71,0:33:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,being somewhat debilitated with old age\Nand somewhat decrepit?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.71,0:33:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Being excused from the obligations of life.\NI really, you know, don't have to contribute anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.21,0:33:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And please let me out, I'm too old.\NYou know, you folks, you young folks have all the energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.71,0:33:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What were we looking to excuse ourselves from?\NWhat responsibilities were we going to use old age as a cop-out?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.21,0:33:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's just look at those things and be honest with ourselves.\NThey're all part of humanness.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.71,0:33:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody has those fantasies.\NEverybody looks at the advantages of any of these life scripts
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.21,0:34:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's one of the reasons they choose them.\NWe have to look at whether we're willing to let those things go
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.21,0:34:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,for the gain and for the benefit that we would get.\NWould we rather be vigorous
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.21,0:34:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,or would we love to have that attention\Nof having a Boy Scout at our elbow as we cross the street?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.21,0:34:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to stride across confidently\Nor would you like some young man to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.71,0:34:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,here sir, may I help you across the street?\NIt's fun, it's nice, just think of all that attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.71,0:34:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy Scouts everywhere helping you across the street.\NIf it's worth it,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.21,0:34:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,then let the Boy Scouts help you across the street.\NIf it's not, stride across with a vigorous gait.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.71,0:34:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Our life, the body, what goes on in our life,\Nis then a projection of what we have been holding in our own mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.40,0:34:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All we're experiencing then\Nis the projection into the physical world
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.56,0:34:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of our own belief systems.\NWhat we're holding in mind is manifesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.36,0:35:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have a choice when we see this pattern.\NWe can begin to realize
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.36,0:35:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,if all I'm experiencing is that which I've been holding in mind,\Nthen I can change that which I experience
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.86,0:35:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,by changing that which I hold in mind.\NAnd that's exactly what we did,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.52,0:35:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's exactly what I've done in my own personal life.\NAnd I shared that with you in my talks on giving up illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.55,0:35:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll just use two of the examples from that talk,\Nor one of the examples plus one I didn't talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.65,0:35:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, the prostate trouble\Nthat is supposed to come with middle age.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.65,0:35:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's a standing joke amongst men in the men's rooms, you see.\NAnd men are standing there,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.65,0:35:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and one will say to the other one,\Nwell, you must be over 50, you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.65,0:35:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a prejudged thing that this is inevitable\Nand it's part and parcel of middle age.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.94,0:35:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And so when that began to happen to me,\NI was already into the study of the nature of consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.44,0:36:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and healing techniques, and I began to cancel it.\NI said that's a belief system, and it has no basis in reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.16,0:36:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Its only reality is that I'm holding it in mind.\NThe truth is I'm an infinite being, and I'm not subject to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.66,0:36:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is I'm an infinite being,\Nand I'm only subject to what I hold in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.16,0:36:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I kept canceling it, every time this belief came up,\Nand kept insisting on the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.66,0:36:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,so I insisted on the truth,\Nand what I did is I reprogrammed the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.66,0:36:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I began to see this belief, you know, as nonsense.\NIt's nonsense, but the collective consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.76,0:36:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, the energy field of the world,\Nits belief in that is something I have to constantly counter,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.76,0:36:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because the world tries to reprogram you again with it.\NAnd so it leaves, and then it may momentarily come back,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.76,0:36:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because you chance to overhear a remark.\NSome other middle-aged man talks about his prostate trouble, let's say.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.74,0:36:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And temporarily you find that you've fallen back into believing again.\NSo it requires vigilance, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.74,0:37:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to begin to undo all these belief systems within the mind.\NThe same thing happened with vision and with glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.28,0:37:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And I always wore glasses my whole life.\NI wore glasses for 50 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.29,0:37:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I wore glasses since I was a child.\NAnd, of course, the belief system
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.29,0:37:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in our society is that middle age brings about,\Nyou know, changes in your vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.29,0:37:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And many people put on reading glasses at middle age.\NSo, middle age reading spectacles.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.29,0:37:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,When we think of a middle-aged person,\Nwhen we look at the Retired People's Magazine,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.79,0:37:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,they almost always have glasses on.\NIt's just presumed that by middle age you're going to need glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.79,0:37:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I had glasses already,\Nbecause I had the image in my mind of the intellectual bookworm,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.79,0:37:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,which I was, who always wears glasses.\NSo part of my image of what I was
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.29,0:37:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,as an adolescent young man was, of course, wearing glasses.\NOf course, if you already wear glasses,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.14,0:37:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,by middle age it's presumed your vision's going to get worse\Nand you're going to need bifocals.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.14,0:37:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And by late middle age, certainly trifocals.\NSo it was at the trifocal stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.64,0:38:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,after having worn glasses all my life,\Nthat I was involved in this kind of research and study.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.14,0:38:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And one day someone and I was sharing with my class\Nall the physical illnesses that I'd let go of
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.14,0:38:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,following these consciousness techniques.\NAnd probably a list of 15, 20 different diseases.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.14,0:38:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And when somebody said,\Nwell, then how come you're still wearing glasses?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.24,0:38:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I said, you know, I never thought of that.\NI never thought of, you know, the fact that the eyeball itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.24,0:38:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,your capacity to see, a vision, the whole mechanism of vision,\Nwould just again be a manifestation of my belief systems about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.24,0:38:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I looked at the belief systems and I began to cancel them.\NYou know, I said, I'm an infinite being.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.96,0:38:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not really subject to any limitation.\NSuch as the belief that I need glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.46,0:38:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And it took six weeks.\NFor six weeks I couldn't see anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.46,0:38:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I never put the glasses back on again.\NAnd during that six weeks when my motility was somewhat limited
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.01,0:39:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,by the inability to see anything more than a couple of feet in front of me,\Nand I also was myopic as well as farsighted,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.01,0:39:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and I also had astigmatism.\NAnd so I couldn't read anything, nor could I see anything distant.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.01,0:39:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,After about six weeks of constantly letting this go\Nand canceling it, and consistent work,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.51,0:39:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I finally just surrendered to it.\NAnd I said, well, because that's part of the technique also,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.01,0:39:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is to let go resisting what the belief system was.\NAnd so I said, well, God, I said, if I'm never going to see again,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.64,0:39:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I'm just never going to see again.\NAnd I just totally let it go.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.64,0:39:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I just totally surrendered it to a higher power.\NAnd I said, whatever your will is for me, I will agree to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.67,0:39:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what is the will of God for us?\NThe will of God for us is complete and total happiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.92,0:39:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,complete wholeness and oneness.\NAnyway, in surrendering to God's will, all of a sudden,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.92,0:39:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in one instant, the vision came back absolutely perfect,\Nafter a lifetime of wearing glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.92,0:40:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So it doesn't matter how long we've had this belief system.\NThere was a belief system that was there throughout my entire life,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.92,0:40:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,literally limiting vision.\NThat was a good more than ten years ago now.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.42,0:40:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And I have a driver's license that says no glasses required.\NAnd every time I go for a vision test, the vision is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.42,0:40:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So those are just clinical examples, just demonstrations,\Nand I share them because of the principle involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.42,0:40:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The principle being that we experience experience\Nin the level of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.92,0:40:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Body is only a reflection of that which we believe.\NAnd so if we address ourself directly to those belief systems,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.42,0:40:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to the mind itself and to where it is being experienced,\Nwe can undo these belief systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.42,0:40:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We have that freedom. We have that option.\NSo let's go back to some of the commonly held belief systems
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.06,0:40:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,about middle age and aging and old age\Nand see how we can be with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.06,0:41:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, because there are two things going on.\NThere are the belief systems about what all that entails,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.06,0:41:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and then there is our position about that, the way we feel about it.\NBecause in truth, it's not the events in life that have any importance at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.10,0:41:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Facts don't mean a thing.\NThe importance of a fact or an event is how we feel about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.10,0:41:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,How we feel about it. Isn't that so?\NHow we feel about it then creates a context.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.26,0:41:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It creates a way of being,\Nand it decides in advance how we're going to feel about that event,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.26,0:41:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,feel about that decision, feel about that fact.\NSo let's see how we can be with this whole problem in mind of old age and aging,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.76,0:41:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,middle age, all that goes with that.\NAnd we'll go back to our map of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.20,0:42:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,where we see we have various energy fields, various levels of conscious.\NAt the bottom, this would be the most unconscious,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.20,0:42:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the farthest from the truth, the closest to death itself.\NAt the top, we have, because of increasing truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.70,0:42:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,an alignment with life, with truth, and with a sense of aliveness.\NSo we might say at the top is God, the closeness to God,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.70,0:42:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,at the bottom is the greatest distance.\NAnd out of these energy fields then come certain emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.70,0:42:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Certain emotions reflect the energy field which is coming out of our position.\NAnd out of our position comes a certain view of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.20,0:42:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the God of that world would have to be a certain kind of God.\NSo how could we look at old age and let's look around us in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.86,0:42:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and you'll see instantly how the world and what you hold this\Nand how you have bought into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.86,0:43:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We can identify at which level did we buy into it and about what.\NAt the bottom with the lowest energy, one leading almost to pass of suicide,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.47,0:43:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and many deaths from old age are not due to old age at all.\NThey're all forms of passive suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.47,0:43:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They're the result of having given up out of hopelessness.\NSo we see a guiltiness as though old age and the decrepitudes,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.47,0:43:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the illnesses are somehow punishment for one's sins.\NOne failures in life, you now deserve all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.97,0:43:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of self-hatred then, the person chooses destruction.\NThey see their life and the world, you know, as the experience of sin and suffering,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.54,0:43:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and they really fear dying because out of their guilt,\Nthey picture that God is very likely going to destroy their soul
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.54,0:43:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and throw them into hell forever.\NAnd so there is a fear of old age and dying, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.54,0:44:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,viewing it as a destructive process, looking at age then as destruction.\NAnd we see the destruction then that comes from this belief system in their life,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.54,0:44:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,all the aspects of their life which they let fall into the detriment\Nof this destructive viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.30,0:44:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,An energy field somewhat above that, but still very close to passive suicide,\Njust allowing yourself to die over not caring about yourself enough to care for yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.30,0:44:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is a field called apathy, with a calibrated energy field of 50.\NYou see it is again a negative attitude,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.30,0:44:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is the one of hopelessness and despair,\Nin which there is loss of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.40,0:44:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In this view of old age,\Nwe consider that the whole situation is hopeless,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.90,0:44:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that the grim reaper,\Nyou know, the skeleton on the horse with the scythe,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.90,0:44:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,has the power over us,\Nthat old age then is hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.90,0:44:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All these conditions are hopeless.\NAll the physical elements are hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.90,0:44:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no point in doing anything about them.\NYou might as well let the teeth rot out and the body go into decay.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.90,0:45:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no point because there is a loss of energy coming out of this world view.\NThe loss of energy means,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.40,0:45:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,now out of that hopelessness and despair,\Nyou don't have the energy to handle it,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.40,0:45:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore you see your life\Nand life in the world as hopeless,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.90,0:45:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and God is really dead,\Na very uncaring view of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.40,0:45:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The next higher energy level,\Nthe way of looking at old age or middle age,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.88,0:45:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of grief.\NThis is very common.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.88,0:45:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The sadness over middle age,\Npicturing the loss of youth as a great and terrible loss,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.38,0:45:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the loss of the vigor,\Nthe loss of one's sex life,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.38,0:45:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,loss of one's physical attractiveness\Nand sexual seductive abilities,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.88,0:45:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,loss of mental acuity,\Nposition and power in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.38,0:45:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,physical attractiveness,\Nthe endless grief over this,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.38,0:45:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,ending up in the emotions as regret,\Nlooking at middle age and advancing age as loss,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.38,0:46:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,becoming dispirited about life,\Nabout one's own life and life in general,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.38,0:46:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and the sadness of middle age,\Nlooking at one's own life as sad,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.38,0:46:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at the future as sad,\Nlooking at the progressive aging as sad,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.38,0:46:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at God as that which really ignores you,\Ndoesn't really care about this process.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.83,0:46:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If we get to a higher energy field than that,\Nwe move into fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.83,0:46:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and today we'll say that the energy of fear\Ncan be utilized in a positive way.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.83,0:46:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What we need to fear is the consequences\Nof these negative belief systems,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.39,0:46:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,not old age.\NThe danger is not in the age itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.89,0:46:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The threat to us is really out of\Nthese negative belief systems that we've been holding.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.89,0:46:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what is to be feared.\NBut the ordinary person fears old age itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.89,0:46:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,They're full of worry and anxiety.\NYou see, grief has to do with the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.89,0:47:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and fear has to do with the future.\NAnd so the mind which is looking at it out of fear
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.39,0:47:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is holding worry and anxiety about the future.\NTherefore, the world, the whole aging process,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.89,0:47:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,looks frightening.\NAnd there doesn't seem to be any God
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.02,0:47:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that one can rely upon,\Nbecause that God could be punitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.02,0:47:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't seem to love you very much.\NNext comes the desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.02,0:47:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming from desire is the intense craving,\Nthe wanting to change all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.02,0:47:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And one aspect of that, you see,\Nis becoming addicted to being young.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.02,0:47:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole thought that life is where youth is.\NAnd so you see the youth cult,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.02,0:47:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the fear of old age then,\Nexpressing itself in a frantic desire
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.52,0:47:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to hang on to youth.\NAnd the inappropriateness then of some people
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.52,0:47:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,failing to age gracefully,\Nmeaning that inability to let go of the desire for youth.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.52,0:48:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, you know, at 75 you buy yourself\Na sports car and start smoking joints
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.02,0:48:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and running around the discos\Nand get an 18-year-old girlfriend
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.81,0:48:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that wanting to hang on to youth\Nand misidentifying youth as life.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.31,0:48:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Life is there throughout.\NThe energy of life is the same
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.81,0:48:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in the child as in the old person.\NWe move up next to one of anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.26,0:48:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, anger.\NThe angriness at the thought
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.76,0:48:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and the subject and at the effect\Nand victim of this whole progressive aging process
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.76,0:48:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that the calendar has the power,\Nyou see, over your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.76,0:48:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, these are all negative energy fields\Nand in practice, really, they're usually mixed.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.76,0:48:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Rarely do you have just one level.\NThe anger is also mixed with some sadness,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.76,0:48:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,some hopelessness, some guilt.\NAll of them tend to occur together.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.76,0:48:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see, the anger of old age,\Nthe frustration about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.26,0:49:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the resentment,\Nresenting the aging process,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.76,0:49:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,resenting the loss of youth,\Nhating it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.26,0:49:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You see young people\Nwho have not had good experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.76,0:49:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,with their grandparents\Nand they hate older people,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.76,0:49:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,don't want to be around them.\NOut of anger, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.84,0:49:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,this is a world of conflict and competition\Nand their anger at God leads to an unconscious guilt
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.84,0:49:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and a fear that God will retaliate.\NAnother way to be about it would be denial,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.76,0:49:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to refuse to see all the things we're talking about.\NToday, a certain arrogance and inflated position about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.61,0:49:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we have, then,\Na way of being with the subject of age and aging
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.11,0:49:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that would be totally negative.\NThe things we're talking about today
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.90,0:49:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,have more to do with the truth.\NTo begin to look at them, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.90,0:49:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,would move us out of these negative positions.\NWe could let go of resisting.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.90,0:50:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We could let go of being attached to them.\NWe could let go of valuing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.90,0:50:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And we could be released from them.\NIn which case,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.40,0:50:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,middle age and aging would start to look okay to us.\NThe God of that kind of an experience
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.40,0:50:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,would be a God of freedom.\NThe freedom to see that perhaps you are the source
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.40,0:50:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of what happens to you in your life.\NThe willingness to look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.40,0:50:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, yes, I'll agree with that\Nbecause my intention now is to find out
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.40,0:50:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the truth about this.\NAnd now, middle age and aging begin to look,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.40,0:50:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the world begins to look friendly.\NWe have such a world as promising and hopeful.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.90,0:50:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We can move up to the level of acceptance\Nin which we're beginning to reown our own power.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.43,0:50:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the thing that shifts the energy field\Nfrom negative to positive
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.43,0:50:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is the willingness now to accept the truth.\NThe truth is that we are the source
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.43,0:50:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of what happens to us in our life.\NWe are the source.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.93,0:51:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,By virtue of buying into and owning these belief systems,\Nwe bring them into our life.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.93,0:51:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is\Nthat we have a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.43,0:51:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute we see we have a choice\Nand begin to accept that,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.43,0:51:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,now it all begins to look harmonious.\NThe God of such a universe begins to look merciful.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.43,0:51:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We can now move into a condition of lovingness,\Nbegin to take responsibility for really loving ourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.96,0:51:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning to nurture and support,\Nbeginning to forgive ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.46,0:51:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that we fell into these thought patterns.\NWhy did we fall into these thought patterns?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.71,0:51:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it out of our own innocence,\Nout of our own naivete.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.71,0:51:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We thought that's the way it was.\NNobody thought to question it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.71,0:51:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,People were not so conscious.\NPeople were not so aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.71,0:51:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only by demonstrating examples you say,\Nwow, looks like I have a choice here.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.71,0:51:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, we stop saying,\Nwell, it must be that person's genetics.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.90,0:51:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Or if I was that rich,\NI'd be glad to be alive at 92.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.90,0:52:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\NWe stop excusing it
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.90,0:52:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and begin to really accept that\Nit's because of the patterns we've held in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.90,0:52:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And this comes almost as a revelation to us,\Na sudden opening of the open mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.90,0:52:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the way to avoid this\Nis to then begin to have an open mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.90,0:52:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to look at the options,\Nthat we do indeed have choices,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.90,0:52:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the world starts to look loving.\NWe begin to love now the prospects
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.90,0:52:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,because we begin to see the advantages\Nof middle age and old age.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.90,0:52:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And many people will look back and say,\Nfrankly, I wouldn't want to be young again.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.90,0:52:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I would hate the thought of going through the teens,\Nthe anxiety, the acne, the unknowingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.40,0:52:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the stumbling around awkwardness,\Nthe endless social anxiety and self-consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.40,0:52:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think I'd care for the 20s either,\Nwondering what am I going to be in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.32,0:52:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and the terrible anxieties,\Nand will I make it through college?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.33,0:53:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The struggle of the 30s,\Ntrying to establish a family and all those kind of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.97,0:53:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of now saying that the past was better than the present,\Nwe begin to say, hey, right here, now in the present,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.97,0:53:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I have some beautiful options.\NIt's suddenly like the whole world opens up to us anew.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.97,0:53:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I can become reborn at age 60. Why not?\NAs we move from a negative energy field into a positive one,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.52,0:53:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,we get closer and closer to the truth.\NAnd we become progressively aware
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.02,0:53:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that what we are is the experiencer,\Nthat the phenomena that have been going through life
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.05,0:53:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,has not really affected the experiencer.\NIt's like we're the hardware of the computer
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.05,0:53:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and the experiences have been the software.\NThe hardware is unaffected by the software.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.58,0:53:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That which experiences is unaffected by the experiencing.\NThat which we are has remained unaged,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.61,0:54:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is not subject to age.\NMen are perhaps more conscious of this,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.21,0:54:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps in certain areas,\Nbecause a man at 70 still finds a pretty girl attractive
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.21,0:54:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the same as he did at 20.\NAnd they'll say to each other with amazement,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.62,0:54:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, it hasn't changed any at all.\NThe inner experiencer has been unaware
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.62,0:54:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that a change has been going on in the body.\NAnd sometimes it comes as a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.33,0:54:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The people look at you differently\Nand you wonder why they're looking at you differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.83,0:54:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because that within you\Nhasn't experienced the passage of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.83,0:54:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Your real self, your true self,\Nhasn't experienced anything such as aging.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.83,0:54:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No such thing goes on\Nwithin the truth of that which you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.33,0:54:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And so this progressive awareness then\Nincreases your freedom of choice,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.89,0:54:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the way you wish to be with yourself.\NYou realize that, for instance,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.89,0:54:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that sexuality in old age,\Nas we covered in our talk on sexuality,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.39,0:55:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,does not decline at all.\NThat sexuality remains active very often to the very end.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.02,0:55:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And personal friends of mine,\NI remember one in particular was a world famous person,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.02,0:55:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,said to me at 76\Nthat his sex life was better
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.56,0:55:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,than it had ever been at any time in his life.\NThat it expanded to unbelievable dimensions
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.56,0:55:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that as a young man he had never even thought of.\NAs a young man he was interested in,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.60,0:55:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, the calisthenics,\Nthe acrobatics, the performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.60,0:55:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And as an older person,\Nmore mature and greater in wisdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.10,0:55:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,he was interested in the greater dimensions.\NSo at age 76, I remember he confided in me
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.60,0:55:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that he had really just discovered\Nwhat sex was really all about.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.10,0:55:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That it was incredible.\NAnd he was just boggled by the quality of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.10,0:55:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,what he had discovered.\NSo that brings us to some of these belief systems
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.17,0:56:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that are so common in our society,\Nhaving to do with what happens in one's sexual being,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.67,0:56:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the so-called menopause,\Nthe male and female menopause.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.12,0:56:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we'll go to a clinical experiment\Nin which a group of 30 women were given an injection
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.12,0:56:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that they were told would bring their period two weeks sooner.\NIt said that this injection was a hormone
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.62,0:56:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and their period would come on two weeks sooner.\NSo what happened was the whole premenstrual syndrome,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.13,0:56:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole premenstrual syndrome,\Nwith bloating and weight gain and belching
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.20,0:56:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the things that the various women complained of,\Nabdominal pains and colics and things.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.20,0:56:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All the premenstrual syndrome came on now a week early\Nbecause they all now in mind held that the period
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.36,0:57:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,was going to come two weeks sooner.\NAnd so we see the intense suggestibility,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.36,0:57:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,this whole belief in the premenstrual syndrome,\Nand the whole belief in the symptoms
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.36,0:57:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that are supposed to go with middle age\Nin both the woman and the man.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.36,0:57:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The woman's belief in hot flashes,\Nall the phenomena that are supposed to occur,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.16,0:57:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,can all be induced by hypnosis.\NAnd it's been done over and over,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.16,0:57:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,where a young person is put under hypnotic trance\Nand told whether they're going through the menopause
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.16,0:57:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and asked what are the symptoms,\Nand their symptoms are reported out verbatim.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.16,0:57:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we see that the menopause,\Nthe so-called menopausal syndrome,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.16,0:57:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,varies from culture to culture\Nand from class to class within each culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.16,0:57:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So what is expected, what is held as the inevitable?\NWe see how the mind holds us then as victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.57,0:57:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though the mind says,\Nthis is how it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.07,0:58:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the situation is hopeless,\None can only give into it, buy into it,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.57,0:58:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,be at the effect of it,\Nand thereby giving away our own power.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.57,0:58:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already, you know,\Nshared with you the example of the middle age man
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.57,0:58:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and what is supposed to go on there.\NYou know, the cold hands and the cold feet,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.07,0:58:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the feeling tired, discouraged,\Nthe loss of energy and libido,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.07,0:58:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the occurrence of all these middle age diseases,\Ndiverticulitis and all these things,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.07,0:58:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and gout and all the things associated with a certain age group.\NAnd I bought into all that,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.07,0:58:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and at age 50 I had a full-blown case of middle ageness.\NSo all these things are coming then
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.24,0:58:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,from the suggestibility of the naive mind.\NI go back to, over and over again,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.74,0:58:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to the innocence of the mind.\NIt is out of our innocence that we bought all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.74,0:58:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It is out of the vulnerability of our humanness.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.81,0:58:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,where comes out of that a compassion,\Na willingness to forgive ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.81,0:59:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,for what we bought into.\NIt's just that we didn't know any differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.31,0:59:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of these talks then is to share what we've discovered,\Nthat we have an option, we have a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.81,0:59:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We are not victims.\NAnd the way to move out of that then
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.31,0:59:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is to move out of the bottom of the box.\NRealize that it is not hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.31,0:59:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If it was hopeless, I would still be wearing glasses.\NI'd still have prostate trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.31,0:59:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd still have all these middle-aged diseases,\Nwhich I bought at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.16,0:59:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to choose then to move ourself\Nout of the bottom of the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.16,0:59:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Just by education, just by knowing about it,\Njust by hearing about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.16,0:59:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we begin to realize it is not hopeless.\NYou see, the mind would like to excuse its own responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.16,0:59:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, well, you can do it.\NAfter all, you're a psychiatrist, you're a doctor,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.66,0:59:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,you've studied all these consciousness things.\NIt was really very simple and I really did these things
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.16,1:00:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the minute I learned about it.\NI took a course that increased your awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.38,1:00:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of the very things we're talking about today.\NAnd within one week, many of these illnesses began to leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.38,1:00:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Within 90 days, there was the alleviation\Nof a great many of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.38,1:00:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I was not a sophisticated researcher,\Nnot advanced in my knowledge of the field at all at that time,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.38,1:00:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,barely a beginner.\NJust knowing what I've talked about today is sufficient.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.38,1:00:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's really all you really have to know\Nbecause I've distilled out of it what are the essential principles.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.58,1:00:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What do I have to do?\NAs though you have to start taking up tennis and calisthenics
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.58,1:00:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and jazzercise or something.\NYou don't have to do anything to undo the aging process.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.08,1:00:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all what you know.\NAnd what we've been talking about today is really sufficient.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.06,1:00:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If we look at this box\Nand look at it now from a slightly different view,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.56,1:01:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,at the very bottom of the box,\Npeople at this level of consciousness here,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.56,1:01:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,value life and rate themselves and others on what you have.\NBecause this is coming from survival,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.56,1:01:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it's having this that is important.\NAnd so a person's value of himself and others is what they have.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.56,1:01:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see certain people as they get progressively older\Ncling more and more to give themselves a sense of value
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.06,1:01:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that which they have.\NAnd there are certain subgroups in our culture with which I'm familiar
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.06,1:01:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in which having this is predominant.\NIt's what you have.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.06,1:01:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And whether you have more millions than another person\Nis really what counts.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.06,1:01:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you lose all your money, now you're out of that society.\NSo it has to do with having this.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.07,1:01:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,As we move up into the middle range here, closer to the truth,\Ncourage, that energy field which sees life as opportunity,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.57,1:02:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that part that settled America, created all the big industries,\Nthat powerful energy center coming out of the middle here,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.57,1:02:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it's what you do that counts.\NAnd there, doingness is very important.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.07,1:02:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What you do.\NAnd here, do is seen as cause.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.57,1:02:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You're important because of what you do.\NAnd therefore, there's a great emphasis on doingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.57,1:02:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we want to hold doingness as the effect rather than the cause.\NWhat you do is coming from what you're holding in mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.57,1:02:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,your belief pattern.\NSo doingness is a result and it's not a cause.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.57,1:02:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't because of the tennis that you're happy and healthy.\NIt's because you're happy and healthy that you express that joy
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.57,1:02:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of your aliveness in the form of tennis.\NSo the doingness then, which is so important there,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.60,1:02:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to fade out as you move and progress\Nin your own level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.10,1:02:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you get closer and closer to the awareness of what you are,\Nthen it's what you are that becomes important.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.60,1:03:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And so as you progress in life, what you have become,\Nit's who you are that becomes important.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.10,1:03:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And so in other cultural groups, it's what you are,\Nwhat you have become, what you stand for,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.60,1:03:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,your isness, your beingness.\NIt's the beingness that counts.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.10,1:03:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And so spiritually sophisticated groups are not interested\Nin what you have.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.60,1:03:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody cares what you have.\NEverybody knows that having is the result of doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.66,1:03:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And doing, if you want to work harder and more effectively,\Nwill bring about havingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.66,1:03:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And doingness, they know, is just a matter of exercising options.\NYou can join the board of everything and run yourself around ragged.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.23,1:03:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So doingness no longer has status or value.\NTrue value then comes out of what you have become.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.23,1:03:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The principles by which you live.\NThe committing yourself to the principle
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.23,1:03:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of becoming increasingly conscious, increasingly aware.\NThe commitment to spiritual principles,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.23,1:04:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and to those things which are universal,\Nwhich transcend the temporary.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.23,1:04:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The identification then with progressive awareness\Nof that which you really are.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.73,1:04:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So this progressive increase in consciousness then,\Nconsciousness then,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.73,1:04:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is not at the effect of the world anymore.\NNo longer do you need to have
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.73,1:04:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and to realize the significance of your beingness.\NNo longer do you have to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.73,1:04:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the awareness of that which you are.\NThat gives you a different position then
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.83,1:04:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,from which to view the body.\NAnd so we look now at what our relationship is to the body.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.83,1:04:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can see it's something that you have.\NIt's not something that you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.33,1:04:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's something that belongs to you.\NAnd so you can begin to enjoy the body now
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.83,1:04:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and see that you have an option.\NYou can look at it as a fun thing that belongs to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.33,1:05:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's there for your enjoyment.\NSee as we let go our identification
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.83,1:05:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and realize that I'm not the body.\NI am that which is experiencing the body.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.83,1:05:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That gives me options and choices.\NI can decide to enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.83,1:05:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see that it sort of bounces around happily\Nand doing what it does relatively effortlessly
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.83,1:05:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,by letting go all my belief systems,\Nnegative belief systems,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.83,1:05:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,about sickness and illness.\NI can be willing to let all those things go
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.83,1:05:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and as I get older enjoy a progressively more healthy body.\NAnd so that the body that I, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.86,1:05:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that I enjoy now\Nis considerably healthier than it was 10 or 20 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.86,1:05:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So with progressive age,\Nyou know, what the world calls aging,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.86,1:05:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the body has gotten increasingly better.\NI enjoy the body much more at 60 than I did at 40.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.58,1:06:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And the body at 40 was very tired\Nbecause it had migraine headaches,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.08,1:06:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it had ulcers, it had diverticulitis,\Nit had colitis, it had hemorrhoids,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.08,1:06:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it had swollen ankles by Friday night,\Nit had elevated cholesterol, it had gout.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.56,1:06:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to carry a cane around in the trunk of the car\Nfor this poor old body.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.06,1:06:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So at age 40 the body was old\Nand at age 60 I enjoy it greatly.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.16,1:06:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,All those illnesses have left.\NSo with the letting go of those belief systems
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.16,1:06:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and those limitations has come\Nthe progressive enjoyment of the body
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.16,1:06:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and seeing it now as something with which to,\Nyou know, express one's happiness.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.66,1:06:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And how we view time becomes increasingly important.\NYou see, because if we look at time as our enemy,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.69,1:06:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,then we subject ourselves to the whole aging process.\NIf we're holding in mind that the passage of time
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.19,1:06:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically, the corollary, the meaning of that,\Nis the progressive deterioration of the body,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.19,1:07:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,then we're subject to that\Nbecause we've been holding it in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.29,1:07:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,If, on the other hand, we view time as the space\Nwhich gives us the freedom to grow,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.79,1:07:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to become more conscious, to become aware,\Nthen time becomes our friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.79,1:07:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over the passage of time, then,\Nwhich has been my friend over the last 10 or 20 years,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.29,1:07:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that these illnesses and middle-aged\Nand old-age diseases of the body have disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.29,1:07:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had the time in which to explore,\Nthe time to become aware that there are options,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.29,1:07:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the time to become aware of how I was limiting myself\Nwithin my own belief systems,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.29,1:07:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the time to become aware of what is that relationship\Nbetween body, mind and spirit,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.29,1:07:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the time to realize that we have\Na complete option, freedom of the spirit,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.29,1:07:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are not limited except\Nto that which we hold in mind.
